race.comment: WHO EVER THOUGHT (1) tough Dubbo gelding with an exceptional record. Was a game on pace third in a solid rating contest over this trip in the Dubbo Cup. Races best with his runs spaced and gets the right set-up again. SHAMEDY (8) reunites with Bronte Simpson and drops in weight after coming back in class for a commanding win over 1400m in the Bundarra Cup. This is harder here, but the figures he produced last start aren't far off what's required here. Can play a leading role. LOCKDOWN GAMBLE (2) only just missed in the Coonamble Cup in a fantastic performance as a 30-1 chance. Needs to back up that performance but he'll be hard to hold out if he can. RHYTHM IS A DANCER (3) disappointed last start but his form prior was strong. Can bounce back.
